Kiri is a greatest hits album released by New Zealand opera diva, Kiri Te Kanawa in 2001. This unique compilation is a comprehensive study of Kiri Te Kanawa's most memorable moments. It features 20 tracks from 4 different labels. Tracks include arias from the Marriage of Figaro, Tosca, La Traviata, and her famous O Mio Babbino Caro. Also included is Let the Bright Seraphim by Handel, which Kiri sang at the Royal Wedding of HRH Prince Charles and Diana, Princess of Wales in 1981..
